Camoflage::

She smiled up at him. "I don't thin we do. I'm not sick. And if I'm 
not sick, then you can't get sick."

The pod that was once a vessal that held the child Camoflage was all 
but a small pile of rust. One small beam of metal rested on the 
ground. The rust had eaten away at the ship. A breeze picked up and 
the rust swirled in a small cloud.  The wind carried the cloud along 
the air currents. It was directed towards the maximal base.
